content:
The **strict lemniscate** uses < instead of ≤:

{z : |f(z)| < c}

This is the interior of the lemniscate. The distinction matters for topological properties like connectedness.

The **lemniscate boundary** is the level curve:

{z : |f(z)| = c}

This is an algebraic curve of degree 2n where n = deg(f). The topology of this curve changes as c passes through critical values of |f|.
